b'       Dear Students,        Link       Volvo Sustainable Mobility Awards includes a prize of INR 12 lakh and recognitions for individuals and organisations making significant contribution in the broad area of sustainable mobility. The award is carried out under the patronage of the Ambassador of Sweden to India & part of the annual Volvo Nobel Memorial Seminar Series.    How does one qualify?  To qualify for the awards, you could be working to make a difference by way of  C2B7  Urban Planning  C2B7  Traffic and Road Planning C2B7  Traffic Management System  C2B7  Pedestrian Safety and Right to Walk C2B7  Bicycle Lanes C2B7  Passenger Information System to Support Public Transport Infrastructure C2B7  Passenger Information Systems  Independent Solutions for Passengers C2B7  Route Planning for Efficient Mobility C2B7  New Technologies for Vehicular Performance, Enhanced Efficiencies C2B7  Clean Technology R; Hybrid, Electric, Fuel Consumptions, etc C2B7  Technology for Environment Preservation C2B7  Safety Solutions R; Vehicular, Drivers and Passengers These are some of the areas in which we have received projects over previous editions of VSMA. But we welcome newer concepts and ideas. If you have any doubt on whether your initiative will be eligible, refer to the document that presents the past winners. We are confident that this will motivate you to take the next steps.  You have the choice of filling up the attached registration form or registering online. Click  here to register NOTE: LAST DATE OF REGISTRATION:&nbs;p;&nbsp;&nbs;p;  OCTOBER 5, 2016 LAST DATE FOR SUBMISSION OF PROJECT IS NOW:; OCTOBER 20, 2016 Register Now!  How does one register or apply. If you have not registered already, there is still time. Click  here to register. Refer to the Terms & Conditions  and Applications Guidelines     Mr. Arvind Sivamani  Liaison Officer (Outgoing Students)  International Relations  Office of International Relations l 2 nd Floor, IC & SR Building  Indian Institute